    "And even if the exact same problem never re-occurs, there might be patterns or trends to extrapolate from situations that are sufficiently similar.",
    "Through repeated encounters with salad bars (Sect. 2), we might learn about good combinations of ingredients.",
    "Seeing the same ingredients appearing in other salad bars, we can make use of our previous experience to efficiently put together a tasty salad.",
    "Following the virtue-theoretic emphasis on moral learning, the same should hold for moral behavior.",
    "In the words of Aristotle (NE, Page 61 of 90 105 book IV, chapter 8): \"[...] though the young become proficient in geometry and mathematics, and wise in matters like these, they do not seem to become practically wise."
